title: Statutory Homelessness, United Kingdom, 2007/08
name: Statutory Homelessness, United Kingdom, 2007/08
description: Association of Public Health Observatories publishes data on the estimates of homelessness amongst the most needy and vulnerable groups. Homelessness is associated with severe poverty and is a social determinant of health. Statutorily homeless households contain some of the most vulnerable members of society. Tackling homelessness requires joint working across health and social care services. Statutory homeless households, crude rate per 1000 estimated households, all ages, all person, 2007 to 2008.
